Ensemble Learning, Theory. 

Ensemble Learning is the main sub-category of AI that this paper belongs to, as it discusses the AdaBoost algorithm and its performance when using a subset of the hypotheses. This is a type of ensemble learning approach, where multiple individual hypotheses are combined to form a composite hypothesis. 

Theory is also a relevant sub-category, as the paper provides insights into the behavior of AdaBoost and how it can be optimized by selecting a subset of the hypotheses. The paper presents experimental results to support these insights, which can be used to improve the performance of AdaBoost in practice.
